<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,310,1481,1507]" box="[189,310,1481,1507]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1481,1507]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1481,1507]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[187,1399,1531,1672]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authority="Song, 2022" authorityName="Y. Song" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,419,1531,1557]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" kingdom="Fungi" order="Russulales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="fusiformata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,419,1531,1557]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Russula fusiformata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[425,512,1532,1558]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distinguished by its ITS sequence with a similarity less than 95% compared to other known species. In morphology, it is mainly characterized by the lavender blush to rosy brown pileus with crenate margin, adnate lamellae, metachromatic pileipellis with slender furcated and septate terminal elements, and fusiform cheilocystidia with sharp apices.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,950,1715,1791]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,324,1715,1741]" box="[189,324,1715,1741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1715,1741]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1715,1741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,950,1765,1791]" box="[189,950,1765,1791]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">The name refers to the fusiform cheilocystidia with sharp apices.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
